FBIS4-59874 "drnes096_g_94004" FBIS-NES-94-096 Daily Report 15 May 1994 Sudan Vice President Comments Vice President Comments EA1505175094 Khartoum SUNA in English 0950 GMT 15 May 94 EA1505175094 Khartoum SUNA English BFN [Excerpt] Juba, 15 May (SUNA) -- The convention of Juba peace gathering affirms the southerners' extreme desire for peace, said Vice President Major General George Kongor. Addressing the opening session of the gathering, Kongor said that the gathering is a message unanimously reached by the internal front to condemn the acts of those who back the continuation of the war in the south. The revolution, he said, is keen to achieve the Sudanese peoples' full desire for a comprehensive peace and stability in southern Sudan. All the Sudanese people reject the continuation of the 14-year war, he added. [passage omitted]
